  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "We assume that unwatermarked tabular data X ∈ R N ×p has rows x i i.i.d.∼ N (0, Σ), where Σ ∈ R p×p is positive-definite.",
    "Denote the smallest and largest eigenvalue of Σ by λ min and λ max, respectively.",
    "Define Z(γ, δ, σ) as the standard Z-score (as in (3)) computed on the Gaussian noise-corrupted table X wm + ε, where X wm ∈ R N ×p denote the table watermarked under soft hyperparameters (γ, δ) and ε i,j i.i.d.∼ N (0, σ 2).",
    "Then, for any γ ∈ [0, 1] and δ, σ > 0,E [Z(γ, δ, σ)] ≥ √ mN γ 1 -I (σ) -I σ δ,(4)where m = ⌊ p-1 2 ⌋ and the function I: (0, ∞) → R is defined asI(s):= s √ s 2 + λ min Φ 1 + λ min s 2 - 1 2 + s √ s 2 + λ max 1 -Φ 1 + λ max s 2 + 1 √ 8πe E 1 λ min 2s 2 -E 1 λ max 2s 2.with Φ(•) denoting the standard normal CDF andE 1 (u) = ∞ u e -tt dt the exponential integral.",
    "We provide a numerical example to illustrate the guarantee in Theorem 2."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Then, for any γ ∈ [0, 1] and δ, σ > 0,E [Z(γ, δ, σ)] ≥ √ mN γ 1 -I (σ) -I σ δ,(4)where m = ⌊ p-1 2 ⌋ and the function I: (0, ∞) → R is defined asI(s):= s √ s 2 + λ min Φ 1 + λ min s 2 - 1 2 + s √ s 2 + λ max 1 -Φ 1 + λ max s 2 + 1 √ 8πe E 1 λ min 2s 2 -E 1 λ max 2s 2.with Φ(•) denoting the standard normal CDF andE 1 (u) = ∞ u e -tt dt the exponential integral."
